---
import VizLayout from '../../layouts/VizLayout.astro';
const title = "2.7 Hashing Bank · GATE DA";
---
<VizLayout {title} currentPath="/module2/2-7-bank" pageCss="/assets/css/pages/1-1-questions.css">

<div class="gd-breadcrumb">
  <a href="/index.html">Home</a><span>›</span>
  <a href="/module2.html">Module 2</a><span>›</span>
  2.7 Bank
</div>
<a class="gd-pill-link" href="/module2/2-7-questions.html">← Practice Questions (10 Qs)</a>

<div class="gd-viz-header">
  <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--subject">Module 2 · DSA</span>
    <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--pyq">20 questions · MCQ / NAT / MSQ</span>
  </div>
  <h1 id="top">2.7 Hashing &amp; Collision — Question Bank</h1>
  <p>Extended practice: Bloom filters, cuckoo hashing, rolling hashes, hash joins, consistent hashing, Robin Hood hashing, resizing cost, perfect hashing, probe sequences and composite keys.</p>
</div>

<div class="q-score-bar">
  <div>
    <div class="q-score-bar__count"><span id="score-num">0</span> / 20</div>
    <div class="q-score-bar__label">correct answers revealed</div>
  </div>
  <button class="q-score-bar__reset" onclick="resetAll()">Reset all</button>
</div>

<div class="q-list">

  <div class="q-card" id="qc1">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q1</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">A Bloom filter can produce</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q1-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> false negatives only</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> false positives but never false negatives</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> neither</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> both</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(1,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q1-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> Membership 'no' is certain; 'yes' may be a false positive due to bit collisions.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc2">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q2</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Cuckoo hashing guarantees worst-case lookup time of</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q2-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(\log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(1)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(\sqrt n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(2,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q2-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) $O(1)$ worst case.</span></b> Each key lives in one of two candidate slots, checked in constant time.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc3">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q3</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">A polynomial rolling hash of a string is used in</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q3-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> quicksort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> the Rabin-Karp string search</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> Dijkstra</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> heap sort</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(3,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q3-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) Rabin-Karp.</span></b> Rolling hashes update in $O(1)$ as the window slides.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc4">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q4</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">A hash join builds a hash table on one relation and probes with the other in</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q4-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="4" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(n^2)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="4" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(n+m)$ expected</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="4" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(nm)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="4" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(n \log n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(4,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q4-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) $O(n+m)$ expected.</span></b> Build then probe, each $O(1)$ expected per row.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc5">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q5</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Consistent hashing is used in distributed systems primarily to</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q5-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> sort keys</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> minimize remapping when nodes join or leave</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> compress data</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> detect cycles</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(5,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q5-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> Only $K/N$ keys move when a node changes, not the entire table.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc6">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q6</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Robin Hood hashing reduces variance in probe lengths by</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q6-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> sorting buckets</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> letting keys with longer probe distances displace shorter ones</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> using chaining</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> doubling the table</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(6,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q6-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> It steals from the rich (short probe) to give to the poor (long probe), evening out lookups.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc7">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q7</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Resizing a hash table from $m$ to $2m$ requires rehashing all $n$ keys. For $n=8$, how many keys are rehashed?</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q7-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">keys</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(7,8,8)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q7-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 8.</span></b> All $n=8$ existing keys are reinserted into the larger table.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc8">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q8</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Two-level perfect hashing achieves worst-case $O(1)$ lookup for a static set using</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q8-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> linear probing</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> a second-level hash sized to the square of each bucket's count</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> chaining</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> sorting</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(8,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q8-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> Quadratic second-level sizes make each bucket collision-free.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc9">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q9</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">With $h(k)=k \bmod 7$, key 100 maps to slot</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q9-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">slot</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(9,2,2)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q9-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 2.</span></b> $100 \bmod 7 = 2$ (since $98 = 14 \times 7$).</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc10">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q10</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Quadratic probing uses the probe sequence</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q10-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="10" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $h(k)+i$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="10" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $h(k)+c_1 i + c_2 i^2$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="10" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $h(k) \cdot i$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="10" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $h_1(k)+i\,h_2(k)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(10,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q10-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> Quadratic terms reduce primary clustering compared to linear probing.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc11">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q11</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">A table of size $m=11$ stores $n=8$ keys. Load factor (2 decimals) is</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q11-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">value</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(11,0.72,0.73)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q11-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 0.73.</span></b> $\alpha = 8/11 \approx 0.727$.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc12">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q12</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Separate chaining handles a load factor $\alpha &gt; 1$ by</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q12-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="12" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> failing</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="12" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> growing the per-slot linked list</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="12" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> probing</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="12" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> sorting</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(12,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q12-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> Chains can hold more than one key, so $\alpha$ may exceed 1.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc13">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q13</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">The division method $h(k)=k \bmod m$ works best when $m$ is</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q13-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="13" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> a power of 2</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="13" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> a prime not close to a power of 2</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="13" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> even</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="13" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> equal to $n$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(13,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q13-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) a prime.</span></b> A prime modulus spreads keys and avoids patterns from low-order bits.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc14">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q14</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Keys 10, 20, 30 with $h(k)=k \bmod 10$ all map to the same slot. What is that slot?</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q14-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">slot</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(14,0,0)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q14-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 0.</span></b> $10 \bmod 10 = 20 \bmod 10 = 30 \bmod 10 = 0$.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc15">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q15</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Open-addressing lookup of a key that is absent stops when it encounters</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q15-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="15" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> any occupied slot</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="15" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> an empty (never-used) slot</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="15" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> the table end</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="15" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> a deleted marker only</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(15,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q15-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> A truly empty slot proves the key is not present; deleted markers must be skipped.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc16">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q16</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">The expected number of collisions grows as the load factor</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q16-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="16" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> decreases</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="16" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> increases</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="16" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> stays constant</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="16" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> becomes negative</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(16,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q16-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) increases.</span></b> More keys per slot means more collisions.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc17">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q17</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Inserting keys 1, 8, 15 into a size-7 table with $h(k)=k \bmod 7$ — how many map to slot 1?</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q17-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">keys</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(17,3,3)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q17-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 3.</span></b> $1 \bmod 7 = 8 \bmod 7 = 15 \bmod 7 = 1$ — all three collide at slot 1.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc18">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q18</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Hashing composite keys (e.g. a pair) is commonly done by</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q18-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="18" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> adding the parts</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="18" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> combining with a prime multiplier, e.g. $31 \cdot h_1 + h_2$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="18" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> using only the first part</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="18" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> sorting the parts</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(18,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q18-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> Multiplying by a prime before adding reduces collisions between permuted parts.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc19">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q19</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">The load factor $\alpha$ is defined as</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q19-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="19" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $m/n$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="19" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $n/m$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="19" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $n \cdot m$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="19" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $n - m$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(19,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q19-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) $n/m$.</span></b> Number of stored keys divided by number of slots.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc20">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q20</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">A size-5 table with $h(k)=k \bmod 5$ receives keys 5, 10, 15, 20, 25. How many distinct slots end up occupied?</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q20-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">slots</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(20,1,1)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q20-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 1.</span></b> All keys are multiples of 5 → all hash to slot 0, so only 1 slot is used.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div><!-- end q-list -->

